<!DOCTYPE html>
<html dir="ltr" lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
<title>BBC Shopping List</title>
<meta charset=utf-8 />
<style type="text/css">
h1 {
  margin:0 0 0 0;
  padding:0;
  font-size:15px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}
ul {
  margin:0;
  padding:0;
}
li {
  list-style:none;
}
.heading {
  font-size:12px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-weight:bold;
  padding-top:3px;
  margin-bottom:4px;
}
form p {
  padding:0;
  margin:0 0 3px 0;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Mobile BBC Recipe shopping list</h1>
<p>This is a little experiment, to help you when buying ingredients for any of the recipes from the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/">BBC Food site</a>. If you paste the URL of the recipe into the box below, you will get an ingredients list returned, with check boxes to help you see what you bought.</p>
<form name="input" action="list" method="get">
<p>Enter the recipe URL below:</p>
<input type="text" name="r" size="32" />
<input type="submit" value="Submit" />
</form>
</body>
</html>
